 Chelsea defender Fikayo Tomori is set to land Italy on Tuesday ahead of his move to AC Milan, according to report. The England international with Nigerian roots is set to be a replacement for AC Milan full-back Andrea Conti is on the verge of a loan move with option to buy for Parma. Sky Sport Italia reports that Tomori will fly out to Milan on Tuesday for a loan switch with an option to buy for €30m, although Milan are trying to get him for 18 months rather than six. On the other hand, Conti’s loan is with an option to buy for €7m, which will become an obligation if Parma manages to escape relegation this season. Post Views: 
